# Chain Breaker AI — Cursor AI Rules
# Every feature in this file must be implemented with REAL logic.
# No mock data. No hardcoded findings. All results come from live HTTP requests to the target URL.
# Read this entire file before writing a single line of code.

---

## PROJECT CONTEXT

This is "Chain Breaker AI" — an AI-powered web vulnerability scanner.
- Backend: Node.js, Express, SQLite (via backend/src/storage/database.js)
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Scan orchestrator: backend/src/scan/orchestrator.js
- All new modules go in: backend/src/scan/modules/
- After writing each file, wire it into orchestrator.js

The scan pipeline order in orchestrator.js must be:
1. httpCrawler.js (already exists — crawls and builds nodes)
2. browserWorker.js (already exists — Playwright fallback)
3. securityHeaders.js (already exists)
4. authChecks.js (already exists)
5. reflectionChecks.js (already exists)
6. ** sqlInjection.js (NEW — add here)
7. ** xssReflected.js (NEW — add here)
8. ** csrfChecks.js (NEW — add here)
9. ** idorChecks.js (NEW — add here)
10. ** sensitiveData.js (NEW — add here)
11. ** rbacTester.js (NEW — add here)
12. ** aiEnricher.js (NEW — runs last, enriches all findings via Claude API)
13. ** aiSummary.js (NEW — writes one summary to scan record)
14. ** emailNotifier.js (NEW — sends Resend email on completion)

