## RULE 3 — csrfChecks.js

FILE: backend/src/scan/modules/csrfChecks.js

PURPOSE: Detect forms and state-changing endpoints that lack CSRF protection.

IMPLEMENTATION RULES:
- From the nodes array, find all nodes with type "form" or method "POST"/"PUT"/"DELETE".
- For each such node:
  1. Fetch the page HTML with a GET request.
  2. Parse the HTML and look for <form> elements.
  3. For each form with method="post", check if any hidden input has a name matching these patterns (case-insensitive): csrf, _token, authenticity_token, requestverificationtoken, nonce, __csrf
  4. Also check the response headers for: X-CSRF-Token, X-XSRF-TOKEN cookie.
  5. If NO csrf token found in form AND NO csrf-related cookie in response: it is a potential CSRF vulnerability.
- Also check: if the endpoint accepts state changes via GET request (e.g. /delete?id=1, /logout via GET) — flag as CSRF risk.
- Finding object:
  title: "Missing CSRF Protection"
  type: "csrf"
  severity: "medium"
  url: the form action URL
  method: "POST"
  parameter: "N/A"
  payload: "No CSRF token present"
  evidence: the raw HTML of the form element (first 400 chars)
  description: "The form at this URL does not include a CSRF token. An attacker can trick authenticated users into submitting malicious requests to this endpoint."
- Export: module.exports = async function runCsrfChecks(scanId, nodes, scanConfig, db)

