## RULE 5 — sensitiveData.js

FILE: backend/src/scan/modules/sensitiveData.js

PURPOSE: Scan all HTTP responses already collected by the crawler for accidental exposure of sensitive data.

IMPLEMENTATION RULES:
- Loop through all nodes in the scan that have a responseBody or evidence field stored by the crawler.
- For each node response body, run these regex patterns:

  AWS Key:       /AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}/g
  Private Key:   /-----BEGIN (RSA|EC|DSA|OPENSSH) PRIVATE KEY-----/g
  Generic secret: /(secret|api_key|apikey|api-key|password|passwd|pwd)\s*[:=]\s*["']?[a-zA-Z0-9_\-]{8,}/gi
  JWT token:     /eyJ[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{10,}\.[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{10,}\.[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{10,}/g
  Email list:    find 3+ different email addresses in same response (suggests a data dump)
  Stack trace:   /(at \w+\.\w+\s*\(.*\.js:\d+:\d+\)|Traceback \(most recent call last\)|Exception in thread)/g
  Internal IP:   /\b(10\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+|192\.168\.\d+\.\d+|172\.(1[6-9]|2\d|3[01])\.\d+\.\d+)\b/g
  MongoDB URI:   /mongodb(\+srv)?:\/\/[^"'\s]+/g
  Connection string: /(Server=.*;Database=.*;|host=.*;dbname=)/gi

- Also fetch the following well-known sensitive paths with a GET request for each (add to existing crawl, do not re-crawl all nodes):
  /.env
  /.git/config
  /config.php
  /wp-config.php
  /phpinfo.php
  /server-status
  /admin/config
  /api/debug
  /health (check for sensitive info in response)
  /actuator/env (Spring Boot)
  /actuator/mappings

- If any well-known path returns HTTP 200 with body length > 50: flag as finding.
- If any regex matches in any response: create finding.
- Severity mapping:
  AWS key / Private key / MongoDB URI: "critical"
  Stack trace / connection string: "high"
  JWT in response body / internal IP: "medium"
  Email list / generic secret pattern: "high"
  Well-known sensitive file exposed: "high"
- Finding object fields:
  title: e.g. "Sensitive Data Exposure — AWS Key Detected" or "Exposed .env File"
  type: "sensitive_data"
  severity: per above mapping
  url: the page URL where data was found
  method: "GET"
  parameter: "response_body"
  payload: "N/A"
  evidence: the matched string (MASKED: show first 4 chars + ***** for secrets)
  description: descriptive text explaining what was found and why it is dangerous
- Export: module.exports = async function runSensitiveData(scanId, nodes, scanConfig, db)

