## RULE 8 — aiSummary.js

FILE: backend/src/scan/modules/aiSummary.js

PURPOSE: After enrichment is complete, make one Claude API call to write a human-readable executive summary for the scan. Save it to the scan record.

IMPLEMENTATION RULES:
- Load the final stats from the scan: total findings, counts per severity, target URL, modules run.
- Load the top 5 most critical findings (by severity and cvssScore).
- Make ONE Claude API call:
  - Same headers as aiEnricher.js
  - Prompt:
    """
    You are a senior security consultant writing an executive summary for a client.
    Write a 3-sentence executive summary of this security assessment. Use plain business language, not technical jargon.
    Be specific about severity and risk level. Do not use bullet points. Return only the summary text, nothing else.

    Scan target: [targetUrl]
    Scan date: [today]
    Total findings: [n] (Critical: [n], High: [n], Medium: [n], Low: [n])
    Most critical issues: [list titles of top 5 findings]
    """
  - Take the text response and save it as the `aiSummary` field on the scan record in the database.
  - If Claude API fails: set aiSummary to a generated fallback: "Automated security scan completed on [targetUrl]. [n] vulnerabilities were detected across [n] pages and endpoints. Manual review is recommended for [severity] severity findings."

- Export: module.exports = async function runAiSummary(scanId, scanConfig, db)

