## RULE 14 — Safety: Never test against real production sites by default

FILE: backend/src/utils/safety.js

Add to the existing safety check:

```javascript
const ALLOWED_TEST_TARGETS = [
  'localhost',
  '127.0.0.1',
  'dvwa',
  '0.0.0.0',
  'testphp.vulnweb.com',   // ACUNETIX test site — intentionally vulnerable
  'demo.testfire.net',      // IBM test site — intentionally vulnerable
  'juice-shop.herokuapp.com' // OWASP Juice Shop — intentionally vulnerable
];

// For SQLi and XSS modules, only fire ACTIVE payloads against:
// 1. localhost/internal IPs
// 2. Known intentional test targets above
// 3. Sites where the user has explicitly confirmed they own the target
// (Check scanConfig.ownershipConfirmed === true)

// For all other targets: run PASSIVE checks only
// (security headers, sensitive data regex on responses, CSRF form analysis)
// Do NOT send SQLi/XSS payloads to unknown external sites
```

Add `ownershipConfirmed: boolean` to the scan config schema and NewScan form.
In the NewScan form Step 1, add a required checkbox for non-localhost targets:
"I confirm I own this website or have explicit written permission to perform security testing."
This checkbox must be checked before Launch Scan is enabled.

