## FINAL CHECKLIST — Run in this order after implementing all rules:

1. `cd backend && npm install` (ensure all deps present)
2. `cd frontend && npm install jspdf html2canvas` 
3. Start backend: `node src/server.main.js`
4. Start frontend: `npm run dev`
5. Open DVWA in Docker: `docker run -p 8080:80 vulnerables/web-dvwa`
6. Log in to DVWA at http://localhost:8080, set Security Level to "Low" in DVWA Security tab
7. In Chain Breaker AI: create new scan targeting http://localhost:8080
8. Enable ownership confirmation checkbox
9. Use auth config: Session type, login URL: http://localhost:8080/login.php, user: admin, pass: password
10. Launch scan and verify in real time:
    - Progress bar moves through all modules
    - SQLi findings appear for DVWA's login and search forms
    - XSS findings appear for DVWA's XSS reflected page
    - Sensitive data findings appear for DVWA's PHP info page
    - AI enrichment runs and populates explanation/remediation fields
